<DOC><DOCNO> ZF310-629-962 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 629 962.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  April 19 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Software Publishing breaks even in 2Q. (Software Publishing)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Stokell, Ian.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Software Publishing Corp. (Earnings).andO;Ticker:    SPCO.andO;Topic:     ProfitFinancial ReportSecond Quarter.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SOFTWARE PUBLISHING BREAKS EVEN IN 2Q 04/19/91 MOUNTAIN VIEW, CALIFORNIA,U.S.A.andP;  1991 APR 19 (NB) -- Software Publishing has reported break-evenearnings for the second fiscal quarter ended March 31, 1991, on revenues of$30.5 million.andP;  This compares with earnings of $4.9 million, or 39 cents pershare, on revenues of $30 million in the same period a year ago.andM;For the six months ended March 1991, revenues were $73.5 million comparedwith $60.1 million the year before.andP;  Net income was $6.5 million, or 52 centsper share, compared $10.4 million, or 84 cents per share, for the like perioda year ago.andM;The year-ago revenue includes $4.4 million in revenues from the PFS: productline which the company sold in January 1991 to Spinnaker Software Corp. PFS:revenues were $4.6 million in the first six months of the current yearcompared with $10.2 million for the comparable period in 1990.andM;(Ian Stokell/19910419/Press Contact: Mary Jane Reiter, Software Publishing,415-335-6440)</TEXT></DOC>